node.text:
To celebrate @elijahcraig Old-Fashioned Week, Lynnette Marrero (@drinksat6), bar director of Llama San (@llamasannyc), Llama Inn (@llamainnnyc) and Wonderbar (@wonderbarbeacon), shares how to make her Three Bites of the Apple, an Old-Fashioned inspired by autumn in the Hudson Valley. ⁠
Get the recipe at punchdrink.com and learn more about how you can raise an Elijah Craig Bourbon Old-Fashioned to support the bar community at OldFashionedWeek.com.
#punchpartner @elijahcraig #oldfashionedweek @rwcfusa 
#oldfashioned #cocktail #bartender

Welcome to a special charity episode of “Tip Your Bartender” all about Aperitivo to benefit @rwcfusa! This episode supports industry workers in need by raising funds for @rwcfusa. You can make a contribution by going to the link in our profile, or heading over to @rwcfusa. To date, the Bacardi family of brands has contributed over $150,000 to aid in @rwcfusa’s ongoing relief efforts. @martinirossius will continue their support with a donation following this segment. #raiseyourspirits #drinkpunchtyb

node.text: Savory, fizzy and refreshing, the Michelada is ripe for experimentation beyond its Mexican roots. From @wayla.nyc’s Singchelada to @diandi.nyc’s Viet-chelada and the harissa-spiced iteration from @gettoastedhtx, @tatbautista explores how the beer-based cocktail has collected a slew of new ingredients, from fish sauce to yuzu to Thai chile paste. Hit the link in our profile for Michelada’s modern look. #drinkpunch 📷:@lizzieamunro

node.text:
The Campari & Soda (@campariusa #punchpartner) might be a two-ingredient cocktail, but don’t sleep on the subtle details that make the drink infinitely permutable and perpetually enjoyable. Four bartenders give their pointers on how to perfect the iconic cocktail at home— from freezing the bottle to selecting the perfect bubbly water and beyond. Head to the link in our profile for their tips on making the Campari & Soda your own.⁠
📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: @chadgaritas version of the Ward Eight closely mimics the original, using the expected ingredients found in the Boston classic: rye whiskey, pomegranate grenadine, lemon and orange juices. Here, he plays with the ratio, using only a quarter-ounce of fresh-squeezed orange juice. "The balance of my own recipe depends on what the oranges I am getting taste like. If the orange juice—squeeze your own!—is sweeter, back off on the grenadine." Check out his recipe for the Ward Eight via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @adamdetour

node.text: Lemon-Lime & Bitters, or LLB as it’s affectionately known, is a spritzy, low-ABV cocktail from Trinidad & Tobago. But as it turns out, LLB has a long and venerable history as a staple of golf culture in Australia dating back to the late 19th century when Angostura arrived on the continent’s shores from the Caribbean. Like many cocktails, its precise genesis is a question mark. @withbrigid explores the history of the easy-drinking cocktail and reminisces on her discovery and love affair with the drink. Read the full story via the link in our bio. #drinkpunch 📷:@lizzieamunro

node.text: @bagchatter's Fast Canoe is a straightforward whiskey-ginger highball with a Southeast Asain twist. A splash of Pandan syrup adds a coconut-like note to the familiar formula. Just make sure to opt for a whiskey that’s not too smoky to let the toasty flavor come through. Check out the recipe via the link in our profile.  #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

It might be the summer of the Cosmo, but this fall, there’s a reason to celebrate the cocktail world’s favorite pink drink. Join Cointreau in their second year of supporting the bar and restaurant community through the “Cosmos for a Cause” program. For every Cosmopolitan sold from October 15th to December 31st, Cointreau will donate a portion of the proceeds on every cocktail (up to $100K) to the Independent Restaurant Coalition, to continue to support the recovery of local restaurants and bars. ⁠
Head to the link in our profile to sign up your bar or restaurant and be featured on Cointreau’s Cosmopolitan Heat Map launching this fall. ⁠
#punchpartner @cointreau_us #cosmosforacause

node.text: Bartender in Residence @blackcheeeze describes the Expect the Unexpected as "one of those kitchen drinks," referring to his culinary-inspired sweetener made with cilantro-cayenne-honey syrup, and aquafaba for added texture and character. Shaken with reposado tequila, lime juice and grapefruit juice, Simmons insists that the elements he pulls in from the kitchen "hit all the points for everybody." Check out the recipe via the link in our profile. #bartenderinresidence #drinkpunch 📷: @haasandhaas

This bittersweet, spirituous drink by @cshumphries features an unlikely trio: Swedish punsch, Aperol and pineapple rum. The oddball ingredients might not add up on paper, but sometimes a cocktail is more than the sum of its parts. Head to the link in our profile for the Golden Handcuffs recipe. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Sometimes a Dark n' Stormy is the only drink for the job. The key to @attaboy's beloved version is a zippy, fresh-pressed ginger juice. “It’s spicy, it’s frothy, it’s cold and delicious,” says @samueljoelross who then follows the drink's standard recipe of using black rum, lime juice and soda water. Get the recipe for this updated highball via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: For the past several decades, the modern craft beer boom has been defined by American breweries turning their backs on Old World styles in favor of ultramodern, rule-breaking beers. Today, however, brewers are returning not just to Czech-style beer—the common pilsner to lesser-known dark lagers—but Czech-style fonts, iconography, terminology and even diacritical marks as a signal of their seriousness and dedication to the craft. Case in point: @schllingbeerco in New Hampshire is offering a series of lagers, typically made entirely from Czech-sourced ingredients and labeled with Czech names and designs to boot. For more about the comeback of Czech-style beer—and the cans worth seeking out—head to the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro

node.text: Few flavor combinations signal summer quite like that of rum and pineapple. In @dutchkills's simple, slightly fruity daiquiri riff, the usual trio of rum, lime and sweetener is joined by a measure of pineapple juice for an added touch of tropical escapism. Get the recipe via the link in our profile. #drinkpunch 📷: @lizzieamunro
